Maintainer: Christian Werner <werner.christian@proton.me>
Description: FieldSimR enables simulation of multi-environment field trial data at the plot level. 
    Its core function implements generation of spatially correlated plot-level errors using either 
    bivariate interpolation or a separable first-order autoregressive process (AR1:AR1). FieldSimR 
    combines the spatial error with a random error at a user-defined ratio. 
    For simulation of plot-level (multi-trait) phenotypes, the simulated plot-level error has to 
    be combined with a genotypic value (simulated or data-based). While the simulation of genotypic 
    values is not implemented in the package, FieldSimR provides wrapper functions to facilitate 
    simulation of genotypes for multiple traits in a multi-environment field trial setting using the 
    R package 'AlphaSimR'.
